.TH MORAINE 1 "2026-06-29" "moraine 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
moraine \- snapshot backup over SSH/rsync and rclone
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B moraine
.RB [ \-c
.IR CONFIG ]
.I COMMAND
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B moraine
creates timestamped, hard-linked snapshots of local files on a remote target.
Each run looks like a complete tree, but files that have not changed share disk
with the previous snapshot through hard links, so keeping history costs almost
nothing. Snapshots can be listed, pruned with a GFS retention policy, and
individual files or whole trees restored.
.PP
Two backends are supported: rsync over SSH, and rclone (cloud, SFTP, SMB,
WebDAV, S3 and more). Targets and schedules are described in a TOML
configuration file.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-config " " \fICONFIG\fR
Path to the configuration file (default:
.IR moraine.toml ).
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version, including the git hash and build date.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Write an example configuration file to start from.
.TP
.B verify
Check the SSH connection, key, sources and that the target is writable.
.TP
.B run \fR[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-target\fR \fINAME\fR]
Run a backup for all targets, or a selected one.
.TP
.B list \fB\-\-target\fR \fINAME\fR
List the snapshots on a target.
.TP
.B prune \fR[\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-target\fR \fINAME\fR]
Delete old snapshots according to the target's retention policy.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I moraine.toml
Configuration file: one
.RI [[ target ]]
block per backup destination.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR rsync (1),
.BR ssh (1),
.BR rclone (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Jonaz Thern <jonaz.thern@gmail.com>
